						               													<description>A party game where you roast your friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BOOM! Roasted begins with each player drawing 7 cards from the top of the deck in the &amp;ldquo;Roasts&amp;rdquo; pile. The youngest player in the group assumes the role of the Honoree and gets the first verbal beating&amp;mdash;take your medicine and shut up about it!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The remaining players serve as the Roasters for the round, while the Honoree draws a &amp;ldquo;Setups&amp;rdquo; card and reads the set-up aloud beginning with their own name, and ending with &amp;ldquo;Roast Me.&amp;rdquo; Each Roaster then chooses the &amp;ldquo;Roasts&amp;rdquo; card that best corresponds with the setup and hands it face-down to the Honoree, who then shuffles the responses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After shuffling, the Honoree inserts their first name while re-reading aloud the &amp;ldquo;Setups&amp;rdquo; card in conjunction with each of the &amp;ldquo;Roasts&amp;rdquo; cards, and chooses the funniest or most clever combination. The Roaster responsible for the best burn must point their finger at the Honoree and say, &amp;ldquo;Boom! Roasted&amp;rdquo; and is awarded the Setups card, which counts as one point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Twofers: On &amp;ldquo;Setups&amp;rdquo; card scenarios requiring two answers, place the &amp;ldquo;Roasts&amp;rdquo; card for your first answer on the bottom with the second answer on top so that it may be read by the Honoree in the order you intended.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Roasters will replace any card(s) used during the previous round; the Honoree from the previous round is now free to roast the shit out of the next person.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The person to the Honoree&amp;rsquo;s left is the next in-line to be trashed by their friends. The Roaster with the most &amp;ldquo;Setups&amp;rdquo; cards/points at the end of the game wins the coveted title of Roastmaster or Roastmistress.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is intended for entertainment purposes only. BOOM! Roasted is not responsible for any depression, lack of self-worth, wallowing pity, OR any therapist expenses incurred as a result of playing this game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you don&amp;rsquo;t know what a word in our instructions or deck of cards means, you must be the type of person who doesn&amp;rsquo;t know how to Google things.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: If you&amp;rsquo;re already an asshole before playing this game, our material is not intended to serve as a form of realistic hazing or degradation. In other words, don&amp;rsquo;t be a bullying dickhead to people in real life.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
